The paper discusses a strategy for learning functions to generate values for continuous operator parameters in multi-object manipulation problems, which involves training on multiple tasks and using modular meta-learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments in simulated 3D pick-and-place tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
